:{{A|VO chapter3 18 himeko 116.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' ...
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 mar7th 120.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' How could a dream bubble be empty?
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 gallagher 174.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Hmph, just as I suspected.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 gallagher 175.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' That old man always had this strange belief in the Nameless and the Trailblaze, and I never understood where he got that confidence from... especially since he never managed to get in touch with the Express while he was alive.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 gallagher 176.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' I could never figure out what was going on in that old man's head, but this empty dream bubble is so typical of him. He was always full of weird fantasies... and incomprehensible romanticism.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 gallagher 177.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' That mischievous old man... Well, I didn't expect him to leave anything concrete behind anyway.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 himeko 117.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' ...
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 himeko 118.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Don't think that's the case, Gallagher. I'm sure Mikhail has left us the most precious thing of all.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 gallagher 178.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Heh, don't start getting all philosophical on me, alright?
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 himeko 119.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Just as Mikhail believes in the Nameless of the future, we unconditionally believe in the Nameless of the past. How could they leave with regrets for the future when they were ready to dedicate their lives to the land they loved?
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 himeko 120.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' There must be something contained in this dream bubble. It's just we haven't figured it out yet. You also have faith in the Watchmaker, don't you, Gallagher?
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 gallagher 179.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Well, I'm a follower of the Enigmata. My philosophy forbids me to have faith in anything.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 gallagher 180.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' ...That's why I understand what "faith" means in the Path of Trailblaze, and I also want to know what he left behind. Heh, I'll leave it to you guys then.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 himeko 121.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Can I borrow your {{Rubi|pet|"Dormancy"}}? I need to make a trip back to Golden Hour and check something at the Dreamscape Sales Store...
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 himeko 122.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' It's for Mikhail, and for the future of Penacony.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 micah 107.ogg}} '''Micah:''' Well I did my job &mdash; I gathered everyone here. Gallagher will explain the rest to you... Take care.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 robin 102.ogg}} '''Robin:''' Brother...!
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 sunday 112.ogg}} '''Sunday:''' ...There's no need for words. You're safe, and that's all that matters.
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 misha 101.ogg}} '''Misha:''' Huh? The atmosphere sure has livened up with all these people in here...
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 firefly 103.ogg}} '''Firefly:''' I brought Gallagher here. It's time... to face the "truth."
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 misha 102.ogg}} '''Misha:''' You all look quite serious... Is there anything I can do to help?
:{{A|VO chapter3 18 firefly 104.ogg}} '''Firefly:''' As I suspected, the core of this issue lies within... the Stellaron.
